Clear.

113
00:10:57,423 --> 00:10:59,618
This one's clear. We're moving on.

114
00:10:59,792 --> 00:11:01,054
Pull out.

115
00:11:03,663 --> 00:11:04,687
They're gone.

116
00:11:08,067 --> 00:11:10,729
We better stay here a while longer.

117
00:11:11,671 --> 00:11:13,502
They may come back

118
00:11:19,845 --> 00:11:21,210
Do you think our hostage...

119
00:11:21,380 --> 00:11:22,574
...will be of any use?

120
00:11:27,186 --> 00:11:28,744
Do you know who we are?

121
00:11:29,221 --> 00:11:30,552
Are you Dorothy?

122
00:11:30,723 --> 00:11:34,181
You people in the CIA
call us terrorists.

123
00:11:35,161 --> 00:11:37,322
But we prefer to call ourselves...

124
00:11:37,863 --> 00:11:40,889
...pro-independence fighters.

125
00:11:41,734 --> 00:11:43,759
What is the CIA doing here?

126
00:11:44,236 --> 00:11:46,363
Did you put the government
up to this?

127
00:11:46,539 --> 00:11:47,938
Are there any more of you?

128
00:11:48,107 --> 00:11:49,540
I'm not a CIA agent.

129
00:11:49,709 --> 00:11:52,769
I'm just an American who was
screwed out of his vacation...

130
00:11:52,978 --> 00:11:55,071
...dumped on a plane
and brought here.

131
00:11:55,247 --> 00:11:56,271
Without breakfast.

132
00:11:56,749 --> 00:11:59,081
They came for you
while you were on vacation?

133
00:11:59,251 --> 00:12:00,275
Hey, Buddy.

134
00:12:00,453 --> 00:12:03,217
He's got to be high up
in the CIA for them to do that.

135
00:12:03,556 --> 00:12:05,114
You watch too many movies.

136
00:12:05,291 --> 00:12:06,758
Then what are you?

137
00:12:06,926 --> 00:12:08,894
Is it common for people in America...

138
00:12:09,061 --> 00:12:11,586
...to be packing one of these
while on vacation?

139
00:12:12,064 --> 00:12:15,124
Sure. We've been doing it since
the country was founded.

140
00:12:15,301 --> 00:12:17,792
Wow, America's the bomb, yo.

141
00:12:19,939 --> 00:12:21,133
Whatever.

142
00:12:21,307 --> 00:12:23,207
But even if you're not CIA...

143
00:12:23,375 --> 00:12:26,071
...there is no doubt you
must be pretty special...

144
00:12:26,245 --> 00:12:28,645
...for America to send you here.

145
00:12:28,948 --> 00:12:31,644
You were able to take on
that thing, after all.

146
00:12:31,817 --> 00:12:34,149
If you don't stop messing around
with that thing...

147
00:12:34,320 --> 00:12:36,049
...you're gonna get us all killed.

148
00:12:36,222 --> 00:12:39,817
There is no doubt about the fact
that you are our enemy.

149
00:12:54,106 --> 00:12:57,132
<i>An anti-terrorist sweep</i>
<i>is now in operation.</i>

150
00:12:57,309 --> 00:12:58,503
<i>Civilians should avoid...</i>

151
00:12:58,677 --> 00:13:00,611
<i>... going outside</i>
<i>as much as possible.</i>

152
00:13:00,780 --> 00:13:04,147
<i>If you see</i>
<i>any suspicious people or behavior...</i>

153
00:13:04,316 --> 00:13:06,648
<i>... report it to the authorities</i>
<i>immediately.</i>

154
00:13:13,292 --> 00:13:14,623
Status.

155
00:13:15,661 --> 00:13:18,027
Some escaped underground.

156
00:13:18,197 --> 00:13:21,598
But it's only a matter of time
before they are rounded up.

157
00:13:21,767 --> 00:13:23,132
Tell me in more detail.

158
00:13:23,302 --> 00:13:24,929
When, exactly?

159
00:13:25,104 --> 00:13:26,799
Well...

160
00:13:29,341 --> 00:13:30,365
...you see...

161
00:13:30,576 --> 00:13:34,706
How many times are you going
to make the same mistake?

162
00:13:37,783 --> 00:13:41,981
We should have become a member
of the United Nations five years ago.

163
00:13:42,454 --> 00:13:44,649
And by now be a respected member...

164
00:13:44,824 --> 00:13:48,885
...of the international community
in our role as an EU nation.

165
00:13:49,094 --> 00:13:51,892
But before that could happen...

166
00:13:52,097 --> 00:13:55,123
...another group came crawling
out of the sewers...

167
00:13:55,301 --> 00:13:58,737
...screaming their declarations
of separatism.

168
00:13:58,904 --> 00:14:00,735
And the main cause of this...

169
00:14:00,906 --> 00:14:05,866
...is because you allowed
the terrorists to do as they please.

170
00:14:08,013 --> 00:14:09,810
If we don't act soon...

171
00:14:09,982 --> 00:14:14,646
...we will lose our chance
for true independence forever.

172
00:14:15,154 --> 00:14:18,180
And we cannot
allow that to happen...

173
00:14:18,357 --> 00:14:20,689
...at any cost.

174
00:14:25,197 --> 00:14:26,186
Madam President.

175
00:14:26,365 --> 00:14:27,764
Your visitor has arrived.

176
00:14:27,933 --> 00:14:29,059
Show her in.

177
00:14:37,243 --> 00:14:39,575
Welcome to Eastern Slav, my dear.

178
00:14:39,745 --> 00:14:42,111
I am President Svetlana Belikova.

179
00:14:42,281 --> 00:14:46,115
Gentlemen, allow me to introduce you
to our guest.

180
00:14:46,285 --> 00:14:48,913
This young lady
is a special investigator...

181
00:14:49,088 --> 00:14:52,922
...for the United Nations'
Bioterrorism Security Alliance.

182
00:14:53,959 --> 00:14:55,756
Good day, Madam President.

183
00:14:55,928 --> 00:14:56,952
Gentlemen.

184
00:14:57,129 --> 00:14:59,859
I have been sent here by the BSAA.

185
00:15:00,532 --> 00:15:02,796
My name is Ada Wong.

186
00:15:18,117 --> 00:15:19,448
Hey, you.

187
00:15:20,819 --> 00:15:22,753
My name is not, "Hey, you."

188
00:15:22,922 --> 00:15:24,787
I'm JD.

189
00:15:25,057 --> 00:15:26,922
Although that's not my real name.

190
00:15:27,793 --> 00:15:30,091
The old man's
not looking too good.

191
00:15:31,430 --> 00:15:32,954
He always looks like that.

192
00:15:34,600 --> 00:15:36,090
Let's hope you're right.

193
00:15:40,706 --> 00:15:43,971
Anyways, what are you
really doing in this country?

194
00:15:44,143 --> 00:15:46,304
Hey, a different question
for a change.

195
00:15:46,578 --> 00:15:47,636
What I mean is...

196
00:15:47,813 --> 00:15:50,145
...being in America
is a lot more fun than...

197
00:15:50,316 --> 00:15:51,442
...being here, right?

198
00:15:51,617 --> 00:15:52,845
I wouldn't know.

199
00:15:53,018 --> 00:15:54,451
The hamburgers, man.

200
00:15:54,620 --> 00:15:55,644
The fried chicken.

201
